                <head>No. 580.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gadwalader</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Cushing</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1874-10-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 7, 1874</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 76.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to your dispatch No. 98, of the
                    16th ultimo, relative to the alleged transfer of Puerto Rico to Germany, I have
                    to state that your action in regard to the matter, as therein set forth, is
                    approved.</p>
                <p>The Department has never placed any faith in the rumors regarding the alleged
                    transfer.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JOHN L. CAD WALADER,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
